CS 361 Group 5
 
Availability for meeting expectations 
    Tuesday  - 9:45 AM
    Thursday - 9:45 AM
    Friday   - 6:00 PM
    Saturday/Sunday: open to potential meetings based on messages sent to the group discord and changing availability.
 
Response time to communication expectations
    Responses should be sent as soon as possible. After sending a message to the discord or teams you should expect a response within 24 hours.
 
Definition of done: when is a task complete? (hint: "I'm done with that but I didn't check it in to github" is not done.)
    A task is done when it is reviewed by multiple team members who agree that there is no further work that needs to be done for this task during the current sprint.
 
Scrum meeting format/frequency and distribution of documentation tasks (meeting minutes, updating task board)
    Team meetings will occur 3+ times a week and will last roughly 15 minutes.
        Note taking: India
        Meeting leader: Jacob
        Task Board: Troy
 
Procedure for adopting policies (e.g. code style, code check-in steps, documentation updates)
if you adopt such a policy during the initial meeting, put it here
    Code on the branch relavent to the current sprint and not on the main.
 
Procedure for handling a member who is not meeting expectations
    First Offense: Have a group check-in with that person allowing them to explain potential reasons for not meeting expectations and solutions to resolve them.
    Second Offense: Declare a specific goal for the team member to meet before the next meetings depending on their tasks.
    Third Offense: A volunteering member of the group will schedule a time to partner program with the team member to ensure that the work gets done.
 
Signatures: each member must sign their name by typing their name at the bottom of the document.
